23/12/2010
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- The foreign ministers of countries in the Economic Co-operation Organisation (ECO) are meeting in Istanbul on Thursday (December 23rd) to discuss opportunities for co-operation and global economic developments.
The regional organisation includes Afghanistan, Azerbaijan, Iran, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Pakistan, Tajikistan, Turkey, Turkmenistan and Uzbekistan.
Turkey is taking over the presidency of the Council of Ministers, the managing body of the organisation, from Iran.
Also attending the summit are the presidents of Iran, Iraq, Afghanistan and Pakistan.
(Zaman, Radio Free Europe - 23/12/10;
AP - 22/12/10)
